            "description": "<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"Boldintrotext\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">Since October 7, 2023, the humanitarian situation in the Gaza Strip has been dire following the recent escalation of violence. According to the United Nations, Over 1 million people have been displaced from their homes in the Gaza Strip, and thousands of homes and businesses have been destroyed. The conflict has also caused widespread damage to infrastructure, including hospitals, schools, and water and electricity systems.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"Boldintrotext\"><br><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">In addition to the destruction of property, the conflict has also had a devastating impact on people's lives. The total statistics according to the Palestinian Ministry of Health show that Gaza reported cases since the beginning of the events 4,137 deaths, in addition to more than 13,162 injuries. Most of the injuries are caused by shrapnel and gunshot wounds. The conflict has also caused widespread trauma and psychological distress.&nbsp;</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">The total cases dealt with by PRCS ambulance teams since the beginning of the events are (6007) cases, including 1464 fatalities and 4543 injuries.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">The health system in the Gaza Strip is struggling to cope with the influx of casualties. Hospitals are overcrowded, and medical supplies are running low. The power grid is also damaged, making it difficult to operate hospitals and other essential services. Since the start of the escalation of hostilities, four schools and eight healthcare facilities in Gaza have sustained damage.</span><br><br><strong><a name=\"_Hlk148628161\"></a><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: #212121;\">Since the closure of the border, 105 Palestinians have been stuck on the Egyptian side of the border. They are suffering from a lack of food, medication, and shelter.</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\"><br></span><br><a name=\"_Hlk148628011\"></a><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">The already dire humanitarian context inside Gaza is deteriorating further, resulting in large-scale displacement inside Gaza and potentially across the Rafah border into Egypt.</span><br><span style=\"mso-bookmark: _Hlk148628011;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">Drawing from past escalation events and historical context, Egypt has played a crucial role in facilitating medical treatment for critically injured individuals evacuated to its hospitals, hosting displaced populations, and acting as a channel for humanitarian aid destined for the Gaza Strip, either originating from Egypt or dispatched internationally through it. The Egyptian Red Crescent is the only organization with access to North Sinai and already holds operations and projects in the area.</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"Boldintrotext\"><span style=\"mso-bookmark: _Hlk148628011;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">Today on the 21st of October 2023, a total of 20 ERCS trucks crossed the Rafah borders carrying aid that is based on the coordinated needs of PRCS, which included </span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"Boldintrotext\"><span style=\"mso-bookmark: _Hlk148628011;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">Six trucks carrying: Medicine</span></span></li>\n<li class=\"Boldintrotext\"><span style=\"mso-bookmark: _Hlk148628011;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">Seven trucks: Medical Consumbles</span></span></li>\n<li class=\"Boldintrotext\"><span style=\"mso-bookmark: _Hlk148628011;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">Five trucks: Food Items.</span></span></li>\n<li class=\"Boldintrotext\"><span style=\"mso-bookmark: _Hlk148628011;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">Two trucks: Water</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"Boldintrotext\"><span style=\"mso-bookmark: _Hlk148628011;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; font-weight: normal;\">The trucks make their way into Gaza through the PRCS, in coordination with authorities on both sides to ensure the safe delivery of items.&nbsp;</span></span></p>",
