            "description": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 104%; font-family: 'Open Sans',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: #212121; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">Since 7 October 2023, The humanitarian situation in the Gaza Strip is dire following the recent escalation of violence. According to the United Nations Over 187,518 people have been displaced from their homes in the Gaza Strip, and thousands of homes and businesses have been destroyed. The conflict has also caused widespread damage to infrastructure, including hospitals, schools, and water and electricity systems. About 3,000 Palestinians in Gaza are still displaced following previous escalations.(1)<br><br>In addition to the destruction of property, the conflict has also had a devastating impact on people's lives. The total statistics according to the Palestinian Ministry of Health that Gaza reported cases since the beginning of the events (1100) Deaths, including (270) children and (240) women, in addition to more than (5339) injuries. The majority of the injuries are caused by shrapnel and gunshot wounds. The conflict has also caused widespread trauma and psychological distress. (2) <br><br>The total cases dealt with by PRCS ambulance teams since the beginning of the events are (2492) cases, including <br>(478) fatalities and (2014) injuries.<br><br>The displacement of a very large number of citizens from the border areas in the governorates to the heart of the cities <br>was recorded in shelter centers or with host families, as the United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Refugees <br>(UNRWA) announced that its centers received more than 200,000 displaced people in its shelter centers, while official sources announced The number of displaced people has increased to more than 330,000 in different regions.<br><br>The health system in the Gaza Strip is struggling to cope with the influx of casualties. Hospitals are overcrowded and medical supplies are running low. The power grid is also damaged, making it difficult to operate hospitals and other essential services. Since the start of the escalation of hostilities, four schools and eight healthcare facilities in Gaza have sustained damage.<br><br>Since the closure of the border, 37 Palestinians have been stuck on the Egyptian side of the border. They are suffering from a lack of food, medication, and shelter.<br><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 104%;\">The already dire humanitarian context inside Gaza is deteriorating further resulting in large-scale displacement inside Gaza and potentially across the Rafah border into Egypt. <br><br>It is Israel will keep all entry and exit points to Gaza, closed for the coming months and as will not allow the opening of a humanitarian corridor for emergency goods and into Gaza.&nbsp; <br><br>Drawing from past escalation events and historical context, Egypt has played a crucial role in facilitating medical treatment for critically injured individuals evacuated to its hospitals, hosting displaced populations, and acting as a channel for humanitarian aid destined for the Gaza Strip, either originating from Egypt or dispatched internationally through it. The Egyptian Red Crescent is the only organization with access to North Sinai and already holds operations and projects in the area.</span><br><!--[endif]--></span></p>",
