            "description": "<p>In the wake of a notable escalation in conflict within Palestine and the increasing tensions at the Lebanese Southern borders, a disturbing scenario reminiscent of the 2006 war between Lebanon and Israel begins to unfold. This scenario depicts an armed conflict primarily involving Hezbollah and Israel. The conflict manifests as a series of intense air raids and attacks, strategically targeting not only the southern regions of Lebanon but also the densely populated southern suburbs of Beirut, the agriculturally rich north of Bekaa, and the border areas, leaving a trail of destruction in its wake. In addition to the external dangers, internal political/security instability poses an imminent risk to inter/intra-communal groups. Scenario Assumptions: &bull; Hezbollah-Israel Armed Conflict &bull; Air Raids and Rocket Attacks &bull; Internal Displacement &bull; Lebanese Armed Forces (LAF) involvement &bull; Blockades and Naval Operations &bull; Risks to Syrian Refugees &bull; Foreign Involvement</p>",
