        "name": "Middle East Crisis | MENA",
        "summary": "<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><em>Since 7 October 2023, hostilities have significantly escalated across the Gaza Strip and the West Bank, leading to a severe humanitarian crisis in the occupied Palestinian territories (oPt). The situation continues to deteriorate rapidly, with increasing casualties, damaged infrastructure, restricted access, and mass internal displacement.</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><em>As of 15 September 2024, more than 41,252 Palestinians have been killed in Gaza [OCHA]. Over 1.9 million people in Gaza are estimated to be internally displaced [OCHA]. The Gaza Strip has been under an electricity blackout since 11 October 2023, and a severe fuel shortage has led to the closure of most hospitals, particularly in the north. This has increased the pressure on remaining medical facilities and resulted in a rise in medical evacuations to neighboring countries.</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><em>Food and water supplies in Gaza are critically low, with only a fraction of the needed aid arriving through the borders. Humanitarian access remains highly restricted, with significant challenges including fuel shortages, communication shutdowns, and stringent restrictions. Safe passage for humanitarian aid remains key to deliver life-saving supplies. [OCHA]</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><em>In the West Bank, as of 10 September 2024, at least 705 Palestinians have been killed and over 5,700 injured since 7 October 2023 [OCHA]. The region has seen a significant increase in violence: between 7 October 2023 and 12 August 2024, OCHA recorded around 1,250 attacks by Israeli settlers against Palestinians, leading to fatalities, injuries, and property damage. </em></p>\r\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><em>The humanitarian situation is further compounded by movement restrictions. This has disrupted access to essential services, including healthcare, which has faced over 500 attacks since October 2023. Displacement is also a major issue with 88 thousands IDPs according to UN reports.</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><em><span data-ogsb=\"yellow\">Meanwhile, increased conflicts along the southern borders of Lebanon in recent months, with a spike in September 2024, have led to a sharp increase in internal displacement, with different reports indicating the number of IDPs as anywhere between 200,000 upwards to the hundreds of thousands</span>. As of 27 September 2024, at least 1640 civilians have been killed, and 8408 injured. [MoPH]. Lebanon is experiencing a multi-layered crisis, exacerbated by the ongoing conflict. The country is dealing with a protracted political, financial, and socio-economic crisis, which has severely impacted the availability and affordability of basic services such as healthcare, education, and clean water.</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><em>The International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies (IFRC) and its National Societies have been providing critical assistance, including medical care, food, water, and shelter. Despite these efforts, the scale of the crisis requires more resources and support to meet the growing needs.</em></p>",
        "translation_module_original_language": "en"
      },
