            "description": "On Wednesday February 17th, 2021, severe and large weather fluctuations have begun; as a very cold air mass associated with a polar depression entered the Kingdom's atmosphere, classified as a 4th degree depression according to the Arab weather scale of the severity of the depressions. The Kingdom's airspace crossed a snowy, \"highly effective\" and frigid air front and snow falls are expected in areas that exceed 800 meters above sea level from the north and center of the Kingdom, extending over different periods and later it will reach the heights of Karak and Tafila, while these rains are sometimes heavy and accompanied by the occurrence of thunder and heavy showers of hail in the rest of the regions in the midst of stormy weather and winds that slow some of their gusts up to 100 km/hour.\nSuch Conditions could lead to houses being flooded by water trapping people in their homes, flashfloods, human casualties, people missing, deaths, road blockages, hindering transportation and cutting power supplies.\nIts impact is expected to end by Thursday February 18th, 2021 evening hours, as per to the strength of the accompanying weather phenomena, such as heavy rain, snowfall, strong winds, reduced temperatures and heavy thunderstorms and showers of hail.",
